divs: Sighting DetailsWe were standing out on the back porch watching the sunset. During the last rays of the sun a big bright star traveled from the south west and moved towards Denver International Airport in the North east, high in the sky. Many airplanes were approaching the airport, and this light out shown them all. IT moved acroos the sky to the horizon and then it moved beyond our view. Silent, but bright. I looked up to see if it could be the space station, and it was suppose to pass over florida, but I did not see it available for view here in Colorado. SPOOOKY.
Summary: Bright Star Traveling SW to NE
